GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 1
HOUSE BILL 1048
Short Title: Funding for HIV/AIDS Awareness Walk. (Public)
Sponsors: Representative K. Brown.
For a complete list of sponsors, refer to the North Carolina General Assembly web site.
Referred to: Rules, Calendar, and Operations of the House
April 28, 2026
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO PROVIDE FUNDING FOR HIV/AIDS AWARENESS AND EDUCATION.
3 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
4 SECTION 1. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Office of State
5 Budget and Management the sum of seventy-two thousand dollars ($72,000) in nonrecurring
6 funds for the 2026-2027 fiscal year to provide a directed grant to Joyful Soul Treasures, Inc., a
7 nonprofit organization, for the annual Winston-Salem HIV/AIDS Awareness Walk, designed to
8 raise awareness, reduce stigma, and increase education regarding HIV/AIDS.
9 SECTION 2. This act becomes effective July 1, 2026.
